<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,942,1182]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
A record of the blacktip tope 
<taxonomicName authority="Miyosi, 1939" authorityName="Miyosi" authorityYear="1939" box="[541,988,978,1003]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Triakidae" genus="Hypogaleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hyugaensis">
<emphasis box="[541,809,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hypogaleus hyugaensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Miyosi" box="[826,979,978,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Miyosi, Y. (1939) Description of three new species of elasmobranchiate fishes collected at Hyuga Nada, Japan. Bulletin of the Biogeographical Society of Japan, 9, 91 - 97." type="journal article" year="1939">
Miyosi, 
<number box="[922,979,978,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the Gulf was first reported in Compagno (
<number box="[238,298,1014,1038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1984.0">1984</number>
), apparently inserted without this authorâ€™s knowledge and on an uncertain basis (LJV Compagno, pers. comm.). 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" box="[316,584,1050,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Randall, J. E. (1986) Sharks of Arabia. Immel, London." type="book" year="1986">
Randall (
<number box="[420,480,1050,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1986.0">1986</number>
, Fig. 
<number box="[547,576,1050,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="39.0">39</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
presented a photograph of the then undescribed 
<taxonomicName box="[1144,1372,1051,1075]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Hemigaleidae" genus="Paragaleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="randalli">
<emphasis box="[1144,1372,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Paragaleus randalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,240,1086,1110]" name="Bahrain" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[279,438,1086,1111]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Triakidae" genus="Hypogaleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hyugaensis">
<emphasis box="[279,438,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. hyugaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Currently 
<taxonomicName box="[569,728,1086,1111]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Triakidae" genus="Hypogaleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hyugaensis">
<emphasis box="[569,728,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. hyugaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from southern and eastern Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1236,1342,1086,1110]" name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1354,1436,1086,1110]" name="Taiwan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[199,266,1123,1146]" name="Japan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and seems to be a deeper-water species than 
<taxonomicName box="[782,900,1123,1147]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Hemigaleidae" genus="Paragaleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="randalli">
<emphasis box="[782,900,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. randalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LJV Compagno, pers. comm.). 
<collectingCountry box="[1273,1304,1123,1147]" name="American Samoa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">As</collectingCountry>
yet there is no evidence for this species in the Gulf.
</paragraph>
